Indeed the praiſes of God were now her daily employ, and ſhe never appeared happier than when engaged in this heavenly exerciſe. She


frequently ſang with tranſport the following words,


"Now I'll ſing of Jeſu's merit,

"Tell the world of his dear name;

"That if any want his Spirit,

"Jeſus is the very ſame;

"He that aſketh ſoon receiveth;

"He that ſeeks is ſure to find;

"Come—for whoſoe'er believeth,

"He will never caſt behind."
